data.title: Featuring Lead Singer David Baron
data.text:
The Bryan Brothers Band released its debut album "Let it Rip" in 2009. Featuring lead singer David Baron on keyboard and guitar, Bob on keyboard and keyboard bass, and Mike on lead guitar and drums, the Bryan Brothers Band jams at tour stops, clubs, and charity events as they travel around the world. Songs on the CD include the humorous and rocking Autograph, with guest performances by world #2 Novak Djokovic and #4 Andy Murray; Spending My Days, Chasing the Sun, Marching On; and the title track Let It Rip.

The Bryan Brothers Band released its newest single, Open My Heart, on ITunes on March 21, 2010. Open My Heart features Counting Crows drummer Jim Bogios, who adds his star power to the band whenever he is not on tour. Download Let it Rip via iTunes.
